When you get down to it, a human shape kind of necessitates a human digestive system. Animal shape is determine in a large part by their digestive system, hence predators being narrow and herbivores being rotund. Some of that shape typically carries over to the anthro variant, so maybe you could say they have a hybrid system as well. But in a reindeer woman with a human shape there simply isn't room for a functional, complete reindeer digestive system.

That said, deer already eat meat. They kind of love it. Some researchers set up some cameras at the nests of ground-breeding birds, to see what they were predated by, and to their surprise most catches were deer. They'd come along and nibble on the baby birds, probably because they need to calcium intake to grow their horns.

On the flipside, foxes have been known to eat a lot of berries. When I was young we were always warned to not eat raspberries growing in the dunes because you could get a fox tapeworm.
